D. Acquisition Strategy
The ALPS program was started as an urgent capability in response to multiple Combatant Commands (COCOM) identified operational needs.

An Acquisition Shaping Panel was held 20 May 24. The Acquisition Decision Memorandum signed 25 Sep 24 by the Army Acquisition Executive directed the program
to a Major Capability Acquisition pathway and Milestone Decision Authority was delegated to PEO Missiles and Space as an ACAT III program. A Material Development
Decision is scheduled for 2025 to initiate the program.

A competitive Other Transaction Authority (OTA) will be awarded for ALPS Mobile in FY25, enabling prototyping and the Engineering, Manufacturing, and Development
(EMD) phase of the program.




