A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Secretary of War (SecWar) designated the Secretary of the Army (SA) as the Department of War's (DoW) Executive Agent (EA) for Counter-small Unmanned
Aircraft Systems (C-sUAS). The EA is tasked with leading, directing, and synchronizing DoW efforts to counter small Unmanned Aircraft System (sUAS) threats while
minimizing unnecessary duplication and redundancy.

 The C-sUAS System Development and Demonstration efforts are in response to DoW Joint Requirements Oversight Council Memorandums (JROC-M) requirements
 for identification, development, testing, evaluation, and integration of technologies to defeat sUAS threats across the DoW. The efforts provide warfighters the ability to
 comprehensively detect, track, identify, and defeat threat Group 1, 2 and 3 UAS platforms. These joint development efforts will provide integrated solutions to meet the
 needs of the Military Services and DoW Agencies against emerging threats.

