       Change Summary Explanation
       The FY 2026 request was reduced by $0.010 million for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and advance the policies of the Administration
       in alignment with Executive Order 14222, "Implementing the President's Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiative.”

       In FY 2024, the decrease of $0.419 million in Other Adjustments was due to realignment of funds to PE 0602212F, Defense Laboratories R&D Projects, to
       implement the Department of Defense (DoD) Funding Laboratory Enhancements Across Four Categories (FLEX-4) authority under 10 U.S.C. Section 4123.

       In FY 2025, the Congressionally Directed Reduction of $6.890 million was due to prevention/enhanced maintainability technologies unjustified growth.

       Increase from FY 2025 to FY 2026 in Current budget request is due to acceleration of activities in Affordable Survivable Technology.

