FY 2025 Plans:
- Continue applied research related to critical Science and Technology (S&T) for Rapid-Reaction Undersea
Weapons and Counter-Measures, High-Speed Vehicle Technology, Undersea Warheads Technology, RPG-of-
the-Sea and Air-Independent Power and Energy. Support related field activities under the Torpedo Field/Lab
Experimentation Program.

- Continue applied research to assess transition potential of technologies developed under the High-Speed
Vehicle Technology and determine program continuation.

- Continue expanding efforts associated with sensing and warhead testing.
FY 2026 Base Plans:
- Continue applied research related to critical Science and Technology (S&T) for Rapid-Reaction Undersea
Weapons and Counter-Measures, High-Speed Vehicle Technology, Undersea Warheads Technology, RPG-of-
the-Sea and Air-Independent Power and Energy.
- Continue applied research to explore additional transition opportunities for technologies developed under the
High-Speed Vehicle Technology.
- Continue expanding efforts associated with sensing and warhead testing.
- Complete related field activities under the Torpedo Field/Lab Experimentation Program.
- Initiate basic and applied research in directed energy for undersea applications, and undersea effects for deep
sea and seabed warfare.
- Initiate sensing, target updating, and propulsion technologies for long endurance weapons.
- Initiate applied research in coordinated networks of weapons and sensors and new weapons concepts.
