Funding increase reflects economic adjustment.
Title: Enable assured communications for the TROJAN Network architecture (formerly Improve security of the TROJAN Network                    0.243         0.243         0.243
architecture).
Description: Acquire and apply multi-bandwidth compression algorithm technology to maximize TROJAN intelligence network
throughput.

FY 2026 Plans:
Will utilize rapidly emerging Commercial of the shelf (COTS) communications systems enabling low Size, Weight, and Power
(SWaP) high bandwidth Signals Intelligence (SIGINT) communication kits. Will continue cyber security efforts to obtain authority
to operate on Army networks.
FY 2027 Plans:
Will continue to utilize rapidly emerging Commercial of the shelf (COTS) communications systems enabling low Size, Weight, and
Power (SWaP) high bandwidth Signals Intelligence (SIGINT) communication kits. Will continue cyber security efforts to obtain
authority to operate on Army networks.
