 Project A9B supports the Electronic Warfare - Signal Intelligence (EW/SIGINT) Technology-Maturation and Innovation Pipeline; supporting the identification, transition,
 maturation, integration, risk reduction, and testing of new hardware/software/firmware (HW/SW/FW) based capabilities to augment and enable fielded SIGINT and
 EW Programs and other related EW/SIGINT systems to keep pace with modern and ever evolving signal threats. Transitions critical technology from Army labs, other
 government agencies, industry or academia to address critical technical challenges and accelerates new capabilities against emerging requirements. Commercial
 capabilities will be examined to emphasize speed of execution and accelerate capabilities to the force. Allows for technology transfer, transition, prototyping of
 generic exploitation capabilities, lab testing, and integration into Programs to provide responsive and agile Electronic Warfare & SIGINT capabilities. Areas of interest
 include, but are not limited to Artificial Intelligence/Machine Learning (AI/ML), Disposable payloads, Tethered payloads, Uncrewed Payloads, Load Setting Techniques,
 Cooperative EW, Decoy/Obscuration, Deep Sensing and effecting, Target/System/Technique Pairing, Common Operating Pictures, Counter Surveillance, Indications
 and Warning, and Electromagnetic Footprint recognition. This line establishes and maintains a synchronized pipeline for continued development, integration, and
 distribution of capabilities across the EW/SIGINT portfolio. The pipeline will support SIGINT/EW relevancy, improved data transfer and networking capabilities, modern
 technique/detector development, storage, and distribution, and HW/SW/FW integration to deliver enhanced capabilities to the Army's SIGINT & EW programs. Enables
 integration and interoperability with sustained capabilities in support of theater aligned Military Intelligence units and Intelligence Community (IC) collection priorities, as
 well as Transformation in Contact (TiC) initiatives, Presidential Directives and Operational Needs Statements.

 Project CK3 supports the development of Terrestrial Layer System Echelons Above Brigade (TLS EAB). TLS EAB is a family of systems composed of multiple variants
 which together provide integrated, distributed Signals Intelligence (SIGINT) and Electromagnetic Warfare (EW) cyber-enabled capabilities to Army Divisions, Corps
