Congressional Add: National energetics plan                                                                                       7.723   0.000
FY 2024 Accomplishments: National energetics plan is to Modernize/Digitize Critical Energetic Manufacturing
Processes. Funding will be utilized to develop Innovative Manufacturing Technologies to enable competitiveness
and strengthen core national security interests, and Enhance and Fortify Energetic Material Supply Chains and
Resiliency.
FY 2025 Plans: N/A
Congressional Add: Sustainable energetic materials manufacturing                                                                  3.861      0.000
FY 2024 Accomplishments: Sustainable energetic materials manufacturing efforts create a test bed capability
dedicated to developing and validating emerging advanced energetic processing techniques to improve
flexibility, capacity, quality, safety & capability prior to transitioning to pilot and/or industrial scale. The goal is to
integrate continuous, and semi-continuous specialty synthesis chemicals manufacturing capabilities, utilize rapid,
bladeless mixing (dual axis centrifugal mixing and resonant acoustic mixing) and apply modeling and simulation
to support quality by control and quality by design strategies.
FY 2025 Plans: N/A
Congressional Add: Textile industry of the future                                                                                 9.654      0.000
FY 2024 Accomplishments: Funds provided for manufacturing scale up of advanced textile-based materials
and advanced manufacturing processes to de-risk technologies and bolster domestic manufacturing to
meet commercial and defense needs. The work was primarily focused on modernizing textile manufacturing
processes through digitation and improved product design, addressing both DOD and commercial needs.
FY 2025 Plans: N/A
